cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper discusses autoregressive generative models and their ability to generalize, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also specifically focuses on language modeling and variational sentence auto-encoding, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of exploration in reinforcement learning, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's discussion of generated contexts could also relate to computer vision, which would make cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
